Package: TaxaAssign
Title: Bayesian Taxonomic Assignment from Match Scores and Priors
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Kevin", "Lafferty", , "klafferty@usgs.gov", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates the posterior probability that a biological sample
    (sequence, image, sound) was produced by a particular taxon, using
    Bayes' theorem. Combines per-taxon likelihoods (from TaxaLikely or an
    LLM) with spatial priors (from TaxaExpect or an LLM) to compute
    posteriors via Monte Carlo simulation. Provides consensus taxonomy
    assignment at the appropriate rank (species, genus, family, etc.),
    empirical Bayes prior refinement, score-based consensus for comparison,
    and automated report generation. Part of the TaxaID ecosystem.
